## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="5f4cf-107">Questo metodo viene utilizzato in combinazione con il <xref:System.Drawing.Graphics.DrawImage%2A> metodo di <xref:System.Drawing.Graphics> classe.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5f4cf-107">This method is used in conjunction with the <xref:System.Drawing.Graphics.DrawImage%2A> method of the <xref:System.Drawing.Graphics> class.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="5f4cf-108">Alcuni overload del <xref:System.Drawing.Graphics.DrawImage%2A> metodo chiamare un metodo di callback definita dall'applicazione di questo tipo per scoprire se gli overload devono arrestarsi o continuare l'esecuzione.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5f4cf-108">Certain overloads of the <xref:System.Drawing.Graphics.DrawImage%2A> method call an application-defined callback method of this type to find out if the overloads should stop or continue execution.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="5f4cf-109">Durante l'esecuzione, il relativo <xref:System.Drawing.Graphics.DrawImage%2A> overload spesso chiamano questo metodo di callback per scoprire se disegnare l'immagine specificata deve essere arrestata o se dovranno continuare disegno dell'immagine.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5f4cf-109">During execution, the relevant <xref:System.Drawing.Graphics.DrawImage%2A> overloads frequently call this callback method to find out if they should stop drawing the specified image or if they should continue drawing the image.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="5f4cf-110">Il <xref:System.Drawing.Graphics.DrawImageAbort> metodo di callback può determinare se continuare o non basato su un algoritmo scelto incluso, eventualmente utilizzando i dati passati dal parametro callbackdata.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5f4cf-110">The <xref:System.Drawing.Graphics.DrawImageAbort> callback method can determine whether to continue or not based on a chosen algorithm included in it, optionally using the data passed to it by the callbackdata parameter.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="5f4cf-111">Ad esempio, un algoritmo potrebbe determinare se l'immagine è stata fatta scorrere fuori dallo schermo e segnalare l'annullamento per il <xref:System.Drawing.Graphics.DrawImage%2A> metodo per interrompere il disegno.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5f4cf-111">For example, an algorithm might determine if the image has scrolled off the screen and signal a cancellation to the <xref:System.Drawing.Graphics.DrawImage%2A> method to stop drawing.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="5f4cf-112">Una dichiarazione di utente di questo metodo di gestione degli eventi deve avere gli stessi parametri di <xref:System.Drawing.Graphics.DrawImageAbort> dichiarazione delegata.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5f4cf-112">A user declaration of this event-handling method must have the same parameters as the <xref:System.Drawing.Graphics.DrawImageAbort> delegate declaration.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="5f4cf-113">Questo esempio è un'implementazione semplicistica delle <xref:System.Drawing.Graphics.DrawImageAbort> delegare.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5f4cf-113">This example is a simplistic implementation of the <xref:System.Drawing.Graphics.DrawImageAbort> delegate.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="5f4cf-114">Verifica semplicemente se la <xref:System.Drawing.Graphics.DrawImage%2A> metodo ha passato i dati utilizzando il parametro callbackdata.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5f4cf-114">It merely checks to see if the <xref:System.Drawing.Graphics.DrawImage%2A> method has passed it data using the callbackdata parameter.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="5f4cf-115">(Alcuni <xref:System.Drawing.Graphics.DrawImage%2A> overload presentano solo un `DrawImageAbort` parametro e non passano dati, alcuni overload avare `DrawImageAbort` e `callbackdata` parametri e può passare i dati.) Se viene passato alcun dato, viene restituito `true` per segnalare al chiamante <xref:System.Drawing.Graphics.DrawImage%2A> metodo che deve annullare il disegno.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5f4cf-115">(Some <xref:System.Drawing.Graphics.DrawImage%2A> overloads have only a `DrawImageAbort` parameter and pass no data; some overloads have both `DrawImageAbort` and `callbackdata` parameters and can pass data.) If no data was passed, it returns `true` to signal to the calling <xref:System.Drawing.Graphics.DrawImage%2A> method that it should cancel the drawing.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="5f4cf-116">Se è stati passati i dati, viene restituito `false` per segnalare che il disegno deve continuare.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5f4cf-116">If data was passed, it returns `false` to signal that drawing should continue.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="5f4cf-117">Un'implementazione di questo callback realistica comporta l'effettivo insicuro di alcuni criteri per annullare o continuare l'esecuzione.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5f4cf-117">A realistic implementation of this callback would involve the actual scrutiny of some criteria to cancel or continue the execution.</span></span>  
  
```vb  
Private Function DrawImageCallback(callBackData As IntPtr) As Boolean  
     ' Test for call that passes callBackData parameter.  
     If callBackData.Equals(IntPtr.Zero) Then  
         ' If no callBackData passed, abort DrawImage method.  
         Return True  
     Else  
         ' If callBackData passed, continue DrawImage method.  
         Return False  
     End If  
 End Function 'DrawImageCallback  
```  
  
```csharp  
// Define DrawImageAbort callback method.  
 private bool DrawImageCallback(IntPtr callbackdata)  
 {  
    // Test for call that passes callBackData parameter.  
    if(callbackdata==IntPtr.Zero)  
    {  
       // If no callbackdata passed, cancel DrawImage method.  
       return true;  
    }  
    else  
    {  
       // If callbackdata passed, continue DrawImage method.  
       return false;  
    }  
 }  
```
